# Android SDK Location
# Uncomment and update the path according to your Android SDK installation
# Windows default location:
sdk.dir=C\:\\Users\\YOUR_USERNAME\\AppData\\Local\\Android\\Sdk

# Or if you have ANDROID_HOME environment variable set:
# sdk.dir=${ANDROID_HOME}

# To find your SDK location:
# 1. Open Android Studio
# 2. File → Settings → Appearance & Behavior → System Settings → Android SDK
# 3. Copy the "Android SDK Location" path
# 4. Replace YOUR_USERNAME with your Windows username
# 5. Replace backslashes with double backslashes (\\)
